@@TJvCustomValidateEdit
Summary
  Edit control that can restrict its content to only accept valid input.
Description
  TJvCustomValidateEdit is a base class for edit controls that can restrict user input and format its
  content. To put a validating edit control on a form, don't use TJvCustomValidateEdit. Instead, use a
  derived component like TJvValidateEdit.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.AsCurrency
Summary
  Represents the Text property as a Currency value.
Description
  Use AsCurrency to read the value of the Text property into an object or variable of type Currency or
  to assign a Currency value to the Text property.
Note
  If the current value of Text cannot be represented as a currency value, AsCurrency returns 0.
See Also
  Text

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.AsFloat
Summary
  Represents the Text property as a Double value.
Description
  Use AsFloat to read the value of the Text property into an object or variable of type Double or to
  assign a Double value to the Text property.
Note
  If the current value of Text cannot be represented as a Double value, AsFloat returns 0.
See Also
  Text

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.AsInteger
Summary
  Represents the text property as a 32-bit integer.
Description
  Use AsInteger to read the value of the Text property into an object or variable of type integer or to
  assign a 32-bit integer value to the Text property.
Note
  If the current value of Text cannot be represented as an integer value, AsInteger returns 0.
See Also
  Text

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.Assign
Summary
  Copies the properties of another instance to this object.
Description
  Use Assign to copy the properties of another TJvCustomValidateEdit (or descendant) to this object.
  The properties copied are CriticalPoints, DisplayFormat, DecimalPlaces, MinValue, MaxValue,
  HasMinValue, HasMaxValue and ZeroEmpty.

  If Source is not derived from TJvCustomValidateEdit, Assign calls inherited Assign.
Parameters
  Source - The object to copy from.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.AutoAlignment
Summary
  Specifies if alignment is changed automatically.
Description
  Use AutoAlignment to specify if the alignment of the text is automatically changed when the
  DisplayFormat is changed. If AutoAlignment is True, DisplayFormat's that are numeric in nature are
  right-justified and all others are left-justified. Set AutoAlignment to False to control the
  Alignment manually.
See Also
  Alignment

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.CheckChars
Summary
  Specifies the character to check.
Description
  Use CheckChars to specify the characters to check in the control. When the value of DisplayFormat
  changes, CheckChars also changes.
See Also
  Text

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.CriticalPoints
Summary
  Specifies the points to compare input values against.
Description
  Use CriticalPoints to set up how invalid values in the control are displayed. When an invalid value
  is found the text in the control will be displayed using the colors of ColorAbove and ColorBelow in
  CriticalPoints.
See Also
  TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.DecimalPlaces
Summary
  Specifies the number of decimals to display.
Description
  Use DecimalPlaces to specify the number of decimals to display in the control. DecimalPlaces only has
  effect when using floating type DisplayFormats.
See Also
  TJvCustomValidateEdit.DisplayFormat

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.DisplayFormat
Summary
  Specifies the format to use for display.
Description
  Use DisplayFormat to specify what characters are allowed in the control. Setting DisplayFormat may
  also alter Alignment, DecimalPlaces, DisplaySuffix and DisplayPrefix.
See Also
  Alignment

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.DisplayPrefix
Summary
  Specifies a prefix to display when the edit doesn't have focus.
Description
  Use DisplayPrefix to set a set of characters to display to the right of the text in the control. Note
  that some of the DisplayFormats sets this property automatically.
See Also
  TJvCustomValidateEdit.DisplaySuffix

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.DisplaySuffix
Summary
  Specifies a suffix to display when the edit doesn't have focus.
Description
  Use DisplaySuffix to set a set of characters to display to the left of the text in the control. Note
  that some of the DisplayFormats sets this property automatically.
See Also
  TJvCustomValidateEdit.DisplayPrefix

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.EditText
Summary
  The current value of Text.
Description
  Use EditText as an equivalent to the Text property that also checks the new value against
  DisplayFormat, MinValue and MaxValue.
See Also
  Text

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.HasMaxValue
Summary
  Specifies if the MaxValue property is used.
Description
  Set HasMaxValue to true to check the entered values in the control against the MaxValue property. If
  the entered value is more than MaxValue, it will be forced to be no larger than MaxValue.
See Also
  Text

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.HasMinValue
Summary
  Specifies if the MinValue property is used.
Description
  Set HasMinValue to true to check the entered values in the control against the MinValue property. If
  the entered value is less than MinValue, it will be forced to be at least MinValue.
See Also
  Text

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.MaxValue
Summary
  Specifies the maximum allowed value.
Description
  Use MaxValue to set a maximum allowed value in the control. To disable MaxValue checking, set
  HasMaxValue to false.
See Also
  TJvCustomValidateEdit.HasMaxValue, TJvCustomValidateEdit.MinValue, TJvCustomValidateEdit.Value

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCustomValidateEdit.MinValue
Summary
  Specifies the minimum allowed value.
Description
  Use MinValue to set a minimum allowed value in the control. To disable MinValue checking, set
  HasMinValue to false.
See Also
  TJvCustomValidateEdit.HasMinValue, TJvCustomValidateEdit.MaxValue, TJvCustomValidateEdit.Value

