@@TJvValidateEdit
<TITLEIMG TJvValidateEdit>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.EditsMemosAndCombos.Edits
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Edit control that can restrict its content to only accept valid input.
Description
  Use a TJvValidateEdit when you need to restrict what the user can type into the control. A
  TJvValidateEdit can both format the text in the control as well as restrict the allowable characters
  the user can type into it. For example, to restrict the user to only type integer values, set
  DisplayFormat to dfInteger.

  TJvValidateEdit is derived from TJvCustomValidateEdit, publishes most of its properties but doesn't
  add any new functionality.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints
Summary
  Used to check a value in TJvValidateEdit against a minimum and maximum value and mark invalid values
  accordingly.
Description
  TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints is the type of the CriticalPoints property in a TJvValidateEdit control
  and defines the properties used to check the value of the edit against a minimum value and a maximum
  value.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.CheckPoints
Summary
  Indicates if values are checked against MinValue, MaxValue or both.
Description
  Use CheckPoints to specify whether MinValue, MaxValue or both are used when checking the value in a
  TJvValidateEdit.
See Also
  TJvValidateEdit, TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.MaxValue, TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.MinValue

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.ColorAbove
Summary
  Indicates the color to use for values that are above the maximum allowed value.
Description
  Set ColorAbove to the color to use when the checked value is more than MaxValue.
See Also
  TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.ColorBelow, TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.MaxValue,
  TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.MinValue

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.ColorBelow
Summary
  Indicates the color to use for values that are below the minimum allowed value.
Description
  Set ColorBelow to the color to use when the checked value is less than MinValue.
See Also
  TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.ColorAbove, TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.MaxValue,
  TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.MinValue

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.MaxValue
Summary
  Indicates the maximum allowed value in Text.
Description
  Set MaxValue to indicate the maximum value allowed. To disable, set MaxValue to 0.
See Also
  TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.MinValue

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.MinValue
Summary
  Indicates the minimum allowed value.
Description
  Set MinValue to indicate the minimum value allowed. To disable, set MinValue to 0.
See Also
  TJvValidateEditCriticalPoints.MaxValue

